f which have not yet been translated, Kun challenges the received view on Adorno's approach to metaphysics, the role of systematic inquiry and the modern condition. As he has Adorno say, the originary impression of shock at the heart of philosophical reflection can only be fully apprehended through an open-ended and defiantly creative intellectual practice.  aIssued also in print.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 26. Apr 2024) 4aKritische Theorie. 4aSpiele. 4aWissen. 7aPHILOSOPHY / History & Surveys / Modern.2bisacsh  aCritical Theory.  aDeath.  aGames.  aKnowledge.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDG Plus DeG Package 2023 Part 1z97831111757820 cEPUBz97831112685900 cprintz978311126530840uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978311126794440uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9783111267944423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9783111267944/original  a978-3-11-117578-2  DG Plus DeG Package 2023 Part 1b2023  aEBA_CL_PLTLJSIS  aEBA_DGALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_PLTLJSIS  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles